title: 5 looks we love this week: Kate Middleton, Priyanka Chopra Jonas, Alicia Keys and more
text:
This week (almost) felt like fashion week all over again with the number of great looks we saw this week.

A-listers were spotted out and about in high style that we simply couldn't get enough of.

Kate Middleton showed us how to confidently color block with purple and green hues, while model Kaia Gerber showed us how to rock a utilitarian style like a boss lady.

Scroll, click or even twirl if you'd like to see all the looks that made us say "yaaas queen" this week.

Priyanka Chopra Jonas

MediaPunch via Getty Images

Mrs. Jonas showed us how to keep florals going strong even through fall with her super cute frock.

Kaia Gerber

Gotham via Getty Images

Gerber pulled up to Vogue's Forces of Fashion event this week suited in booted in an olive green look from Alexander McQueen paired perfectly with Jimmy Choo shoes.

Kate Middleton

Max Mumby/indigo via Getty Images

If anyone knows how to stylishly stroll in a pair of trousers, it's the Duchess of Cambridge. She showed off how to work purple and green like a true queen.

Anne Hathaway

Theo Wargo/Getty Images

Hathaway looked regal in her cream-colored look worn on the red carpet at Amazon's Museum Of Modern Love.

Alicia Keys

Paul Archuleta/FilmMagic

Keys is pretty and polished while flawlessly flaunting a black and white outfit along with a stunning sparkly clutch.
description: Check out five great outfits from this week from Kate Middleton, Priyanka Chopra Jonas, and Alicia Keys.
